TaggingRules->{
 "ModificationHighlight" -> False, "ColorType" -> "", "LinkTrails" -> "", 
  "ExampleCounter" -> 1, 
  "Openers" -> {
   "PrimaryExamplesSection" -> Open, "ExampleSection" -> {"0" -> Open}}, 
  "NewStyles" -> True, "CitationPopupData" -> {"2022", ""}, "ShowCitation" -> 
  False, "RootCaptions" -> "", "HeaderCoreAreaLink" -> {}, 
  "Metadata" -> {
   "built" -> "{2026, 4, 12, 18, 0, 2.193149}", 
    "history" -> {"13.1", "", "", ""}, "context" -> "QuantumMob`Q3`", 
    "keywords" -> {"symmetric group", "permutation group"}, 
    "specialkeywords" -> {}, "tutorialcollectionlinks" -> {}, "index" -> True,
     "label" -> "Quantum Mob/ Q3 Tech Note", "language" -> "en", "paclet" -> 
    "QuantumMob/Q3", "status" -> "None", "summary" -> 
    "PermtuationMatrix is a realization of the permutation representation of \
the symmetric group S_n associated with set {1,2,\\[Ellipsis], n}. In this \
document, the relation between the built-in PermutationMatrix and permutation \
representation is explained in detail. See also Definition 1.3.2 of Sagan \
(2001). A permutation \
\\[Sigma]:{1,2,\\[Ellipsis],n}\\[RightArrow]{1,2,\\[Ellipsis],n} is an \
one-to-one correspondence k\\[RightTeeArrow]\\[Sigma] (k). When it is \
regarded as a group element, its action on a set defined by {y_ 1,y_ \
2,\\[Ellipsis],y_n}:=\\[Sigma]{x_ 1,x_ 2,\\[Ellipsis],x_n}=Permute[{x_ 1,x_ \
2,\\[Ellipsis],x_n},\\[Sigma]] returns {y_ 1,y_ 2,\\[Ellipsis],y_n} with \
y_k=x_\\[Sigma]^-1(k) ; that is, x_k is moved to position \\[Sigma](k) of the \
output list y so that x_k\\[RightTeeArrow]y_\\[Sigma] (k).", "synonyms" -> {},
     "tabletags" -> {}, "title" -> "Permutation Representation", 
    "titlemodifier" -> "", "metadescription" -> "", "windowtitle" -> 
    "Permutation Representation", "type" -> "Tech Note", "uri" -> 
    "QuantumMob/Q3/tutorial/PermutationRepresentation"}},
